---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ContactSection from "@components/ContactSection.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Self-Defence Karate | Seishinkai Self-Defence"
  description="Self-defence in Sapporo, health karate, Seishinkai self-defence"
  lang="en"
  path="/en/membership/self-defence/"
>
  <section class="dojo-list">
    <div class="page-container">
      <div class="section__title-area">
        <span class="section-label">SELF-DEFENCE</span>
        <h1 class="section-title">
          Fitness, Health, and Practical Self-Defence Through Karate
        </h1>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-page__lead">
        Seishinkai Karate combines three essential elements: "Fitness Karate,"
        which helps improve physical ability and supports healthy development;
        "Health Karate," which uses full-body movement and breathing exercises
        to promote overall wellness; and "Self-Defence Karate," which teaches
        practical techniques such as joint locks, balance breaking, and vital
        point control. In addition to our regular classes, we also provide
        seminars for companies, schools, and community groups upon request.
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">
        ▼Self-Defence Seminars in Sapporo
      </h2>

      <div class="detail-gallery">

        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/self-defence/goshi1.jpg"
            alt=""
            width="416"
            height="296"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Self-Defence Seminar at Sapporo Women's Junior College
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/self-defence/goshin2.jpg"
            alt=""
            width="416"
            height="296"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Self-Defence Seminar for Female Employees of Goda Kanko Co., Ltd.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/self-defence/goshin3.jpg"
            alt=""
            width="416"
            height="296"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Self-Defence Seminar at The Mainichi Newspapers
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/self-defence/goshin4.jpg"
            alt=""
            width="416"
            height="296"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Couleur Mama's College Self-Defence Seminar
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/self-defence/goshin5.jpg"
            alt=""
            width="416"
            height="296"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Self-Defence Seminar for the Stylists Association
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/self-defence/goshin6.jpg"
            alt=""
            width="416"
            height="296"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Self-Defence Seminar for the Council of Social Welfare
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

      </div>

      <p class="detail-page__note">
        Japan is known for being one of the safest countries in the world, but
        no place can be considered completely risk-free. We believe everyone
        can benefit from learning practical skills to avoid and respond to
        dangerous situations. Individuals can participate through our <a href="/en/dojo/kobetsu/">private
        lesson</a> program.
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">
        ▼Health Karate Seminars & Wellness Classes
      </h2>

      <div class="detail-gallery">

        <div class="detail-media">
          <a href="/en/dojo/kenko/">
            <img
              src="/assets/images/self-defence/kenko1.jpg"
              alt=""
              width="416"
              height="296"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
          <p class="detail-media__caption">
            Health Karate Exercise Class at a Community Center
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-media">
          <a href="/en/dojo/kenko/">
            <img
              src="/assets/images/self-defence/kenko2.jpg"
              alt=""
              width="416"
              height="296"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
          <p class="detail-media__caption">
            Health Seminar at Yawaragi Funeral Hall
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-media">
          <a
            href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZCHhYSfjGMU"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
          >
            <img
              src="/assets/images/self-defence/kenko3.jpg"
              alt=""
              width="416"
              height="296"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
          <p class="detail-media__caption">
            J:COM Health Karate Seminar
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <p class="detail-page__note">
        Seishinkai Health Karate is designed as a gentle full-body exercise
        program that improves mobility without placing excessive strain on the
        joints, making it especially suitable for seniors. Trial classes
        (¥500) are held every Monday and Wednesday from 2:00 PM at our
        headquarters. We offer both <a href="/en/dojo/exe/">private</a> and <a href="/en/dojo/hq/">regular</a> membership classes,
        and a new <a href="/en/dojo/kenko/">health exercise program</a> is also available.
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">
        ◆Seminars
      </h2>

      <p class="detail-page__note">
        We offer Health Karate Seminars, Women's Self-Defence Seminars, and
        seminars for companies, schools, and other organizations when five or
        more participants are registered.<br />
        Fees:<br />
        5–9 participants: ¥3,000 per person<br />
        10 or more participants: ¥2,500 per person<br />
        Private lesson: ¥5,000<br /><br />
        For more information, please contact the Seishinkai office by email.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

  <ContactSection>
</BaseLayout>